{"questionId":"22520801","questionHtml":"<p>By considering&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cosec</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></msqrt></math>, deduce that the curve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></msqrt></math>&nbsp;has a positive gradient for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>y</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cosec</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></msqrt><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></msqrt><mo> </mo><mi>cosec</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cosec</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msqrt><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></msqrt><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;(for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so the curve has a positive gradient for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>R0A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22520801","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ2.12f","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"By considering dydx-y cosec 2x=tan x, deduce that the curve y=xtan x has a positive gradient for 0<x<π2.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.2—Increasing and decreasing functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}